==Math==
Nagato/Mutsu: [99 (base FP) + 31.5 (51 proto FP) + 25 (22 proto FP) + 11 (AP shell FP) + 5 (daytime FP bonus)] * 1.1 (trident multiplier) * .8 (head-on multipler) = 150.92 daytime FP.

Roma: [105 (base FP) + 25.743*2 (381mm kai FP) + 11.1623 (AP shell FP) + 5 (daytime FP bonus)] * 1.1 (trident multiplier) * .8 (head-on multiplier) = 151.93 daytime FP

Italia: [102 (base FP) + 25.743*2 (381mm kai FP) + 11.1623 (AP shell FP) + 5 (daytime FP bonus)] * 1.1 (trident multiplier) * .8 (head-on multiplier) = 149.29 daytime FP.

==Notes==
*According to [https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1uV4MVs0uz5CicCdO6vunu5JFI8oZO7V38TCMO2BHSMY/htmlview tests], 51 proto does not have overweight penalties or fit bonuses on Nagato-class or Yamato-class.
*By using [[Ro.43_Reconnaissance_Seaplane]] on Italia, you can reach the 150 head-on FP cap in exchange for a lower Artillery Spotting Rate.

